1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper focuses on the modeling and analysis of a multi-tier network with small cells, which is a key area of research in networking and internet architecture. 
2. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper discusses the signal to interference plus noise ratio (SINR) coverage probability, which is a key concept in information theory. 
3. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper discusses the use of millimeter-wave (mm-wave) bands, which is a key area of research in multimedia communication. 
4. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper discusses the deployment density of small cells and the RAT selection probabilities, which are related to system and control aspects of the network. 
5. cs.COM (Computers and Society) - While less likely, the paper could also be relevant to the societal impact of small cell deployment and the use of mm-wave bands in communication networks.
